    "Examination": {
      "text": "Hand xrays",
      "subsections": {
        "Hand_Examination": {
          "text": "Assess angulation\n[1]\nHead-to-neck angle of the metacarpals is normally 15 degrees\nFracture angulation = measured angle minus 15 deg\nAngle toleration (below which there is no adverse functional outcome)\n2nd MC < 10 deg\n3rd MC < 20 deg\n4th MC < 30 deg\n5th MC < 30-40 deg\nAssess rotational alignment by looking for overlap of the 5th over the 4th digit (scissoring or psuedoscissoring)\nAssess extensor apparatus\nAssess skin integrity",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
